<p>Hey hey! So, right now, there's not really a guide to making a theme quite yet, unfortunately. It's something I plan to do soon™ but haven't quite gotten to it yet.</p>
<p>In the meantime, the best way to learn how to theme it is to look at the other themes, particularly the ones that have their code in collapsible at the bottom of their page, and seeing how they're made.</p>
<p>The thing I suggest is to nab the <a href="https://github.com/Nu-SCPTheme/Black-Highlighter/tree/master/src/css">root.css file from our Github</a> and editing the :root vars there first. A large amount of the theme can be edited purely through these :root vars.</p>
<p>If you have any questions or need any help feel free to reach out to me on Discord!</p>

